author: Just Jared
title: 'Lego Batman Movie' Dominates 'Fifty Shades Darker' at Weekend Box Office
text:
Tweet 'Lego Batman Movie' Dominates 'Fifty Shades Darker' at Weekend Box Office 
The Lego Batman Movie was the most lucrative movie at the box office this weekend, earning $55.6 million total. 
The Will Arnett -starrer ended up selling about $93 million total in tickets around the world. 
Taking second at the box office was Dakota Johnson and Jamie Dornan â€˜s Fifty Shades Darker , the sequel to Fifty Shades of Grey . The film took in $46.8 million domestically, and another $100.1 million worldwide. The first movie made $570 million worldwide. 
John Wick: Chapter Two earned $30.0 million in its opening weekend. 
Rounding out the top five are Split with $9.3 million and Hidden Figures at $8 million, EW reports.
